cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Cognito — Cognitive Operating System for Claude Code"
message: "If you use Cognito in academic work or derived projects, please cite it as below."
type: software
version: 1.1.0
date-released: "2026-04-18"
license: MIT
url: "https://github.com/Luispitik/cognito"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Luispitik/cognito"
abstract: >
  Cognito is a cognitive operating system that orchestrates seven thinking
  modes across five project phases for Claude Code, with deterministic hooks
  on critical gates and creative latitude elsewhere. It addresses two known
  LLM biases — anchoring and premature convergence — by activating the right
  thinking mode at the right phase, blocking anti-patterns with shell-based
  gates, and exposing audience-specific profiles (operator, student, public,
  client).
